trans-unit.source: Represents a single user interface (UI) entity managed by an <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Adorner" />.
trans-unit.target: Représente une seule entité d'interface utilisateur gérée par <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Adorner" />.

trans-unit.source: The sole purpose of a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> is to paint and hit test.
trans-unit.target: Le seul but d’un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> est pour le dessin et le test de positionnement.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> does not have a window handle (HWND), as it is rendered on the adorner window control of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.
trans-unit.target: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> n’a pas d’un handle de fenêtre (HWND), tel qu’il est rendu sur le contrôle de fenêtre de dispositif d’ornement de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.

trans-unit.source: Each <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> can have a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> associated with it.
trans-unit.target: Chaque <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> peut avoir un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> associé.

trans-unit.source: A successfully hit-tested <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> has the opportunity to push a new or different <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> onto the behavior stack of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.
trans-unit.target: Un a été testé <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> a la possibilité d’envoyer un nouveau ou différent <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> dans la pile de comportement de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Behavior Service Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7c60cc41-4324-46b5-b444-b39eda7cb33f).
trans-unit.target: Pour plus d’informations, consultez [vue d’ensemble du Service de comportement](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7c60cc41-4324-46b5-b444-b39eda7cb33f).

trans-unit.target: Fournit la logique de tests de positionnement.

trans-unit.source: A <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor" /> if the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph" /> is associated with <paramref name="p" />; otherwise, <see langword="null" />.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor" /> si le <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph" /> est associé au <paramref name="p" /> ; sinon, <see langword="null" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph.GetHitTest%2A> method is an `abstract` method that forces <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> implementations to provide hit test logic.
trans-unit.target: Le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph.GetHitTest%2A> méthode est un `abstract` méthode force <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> implémentations pour fournir la logique de test de positionnement.

trans-unit.source: Given any point, if the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> has decided to be involved with that location, it will need to return a valid <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor>.
trans-unit.target: N’importe quel point donné, si le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> a décidé d’intervenir au niveau de cet emplacement, il doit retourner un élément valide <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor>.

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, returning `null` will cause the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService> to ignore the location.
trans-unit.target: Sinon, retourner `null` entraîne la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService> ignore l’emplacement.
